# macOS Finder duplicate artifacts
# Pattern: "name 2.ext" (e.g. "README 2.md", "cli 2.py", "chart 2.png").
# Finder creates these when copying into a folder that already contains
# a file with the target name. They're not real code/data; they pollute
# `git status` with hundreds of spurious untracked entries. Safe to
# ignore at the repo level — nothing in git history references them.
* [0-9].py
* [0-9].md
* [0-9].png
* [0-9].txt
* [0-9].pptx
* [0-9].docx
* [0-9].xlsx
* [0-9].json
* [0-9].yaml
* [0-9].yml
* [0-9].csv
* [0-9].html
* [0-9].css
* [0-9].js
* [0-9].gitignore
.gitignore [0-9]
